This test appears to depend on optional graph backends (e.g., `pygraphviz` and/or `pydot`). If CI doesn’t install either dependency, the entire test module can fail before exercising the new regression test. Consider making this test robust to missing optional deps by using `pytest.importorskip` (e.g., skip unless `pygraphviz` or `pydot` is available), or otherwise gating the test so CI can still run the rest of the suite.
```suggestion
    def test_build_graph_from_str(self):
        try:
            __import__("pygraphviz")
        except ImportError:
            pytest.importorskip("pydot")
```

