While we can keep the two different plotting files for now, it will be good to only use one of the graphviz libraries (graphviz or pygraphviz). This is to avoid confusion for the users of v0.8--will be awkward to ask them to install two plot libraries.

[pydot](https://github.com/pydot/pydot) is another contender. Its benefit is that it is pure python and networkx can directly output a pydot graph. `graph = networkx.drawing.nx_pydot.to_pydot(my_networkx_graph)`. Can you check if it is possible to write this code in pydot?

@petergtz Any thoughts here? Will be nice to converge to one library.

That is a problem. At the moment, I have implemented only the ability to make use of a function. I was thinking we could make use of a wrapper function on top of the original in the case of a list or a tuple. For example:
```
def _true_causal_effect(self, treatment):
    if  callable( self.true_causal_effect ):
         return self.true_causal_effect(treatment)
     else:
          return np.dot( np.array(self.true_causal_effect), treatment)
```
